02/10/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Defence Minister Ioan Mircea Pascu and his Latvian counterpart, Girtis Valdis Kristovskis, met in Bucharest on Wednesday (1 October) to discuss issues related to national defence planning after joining NATO.
They also discussed bilateral co-operation in the military sector.
This was their third meeting in less than a year.
(ACT Media - 02/10/03;
Rompres - 01/10/03)
